            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2118.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2118.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2118.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the butternut squash is cooking, add the <strong>Thai rice noodles</strong> to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Set aside for 12-15 min or until softened</p>\n<p>Once softened, drain the noodles reserving a cup of <strong>starchy noodle water<br /></strong><br />Drizzle with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (this prevents the noodles from sticking together!) and set aside</p>",
